# Secrets — NEVER commit. README §5 documents this exclusion as a security
# guarantee; this file makes the guarantee true the instant a consumer copies
# the template into their own repo. Also covers in-place dogfooding by
# claude-workflow maintainers running `wrangler dev` against a real
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY in .dev.vars.
#
# Why .dev.vars matters: wrangler's local dev mode reads from .dev.vars
# instead of `wrangler secret`-bound values. A maintainer creating one with
# a live sk-or-v1-… key would otherwise be one `git add .` away from a
# committed credential.
.dev.vars
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Generated by `npm install` / `wrangler dev`
node_modules/
.wrangler/

# Build artifacts (none today, but `wrangler deploy` may emit to .wrangler/dist)
dist/
